ou would expect for the following.\n\n(a) The average speed of a train and the time taken for a journey.\n\n(b) The distance travelled by a car and the amount of fuel used.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q13","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":13,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.3","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Scale drawings and bearings","qtype":"scale drawings and bearings","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q13","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The scale drawing shows a rock, R.\nThe scale is 1 centimetre represents 30 metres.\nA lighthouse, L, is 210 m from R, on a bearing of 125°.\n\nOn the diagram, mark the position of L.\n\n%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"other"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q14","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":14,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q14","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Rearrange $2(w + h) = P$ to make $w$ the subject.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"rearrange","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$w$ ="}},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q15","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":15,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q15","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Genaro measures the length, $l$ cm, of his desk as 120 cm, correct to the nearest centimetre.\n\nComplete the statement about the value of $l$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"119.5","suffix":"l"}},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q16","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":16,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q16","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Solve.\n$7x - 5 = 16$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$x$ ="}},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q17","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":17,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q17","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Without using a calculator, work out $\\dfrac{12}{7} \\div \\dfrac{35}{9}$.\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q18","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":18,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.4","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Similarity and congruence","qtype":"similarity and congruence","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q18","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Shape ABCD is similar to shape PQRS.\n\n%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\nWork out the value of $a$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$a$ ="}},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q19","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":19,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.13","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Percentages","qtype":"percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q19","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Harry invests \\$800 for 2 years at a rate of 3\\% per year compound interest.\n\nCalculate the amount of interest he receives at the end of the 2 years.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q20","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":20,"marks":3,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q20","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Solve the simultaneous equations.\nYou must show all your working.\n\\begin{align*}\n5x - 2y &= 26 \\\\\n7x + 6y &= 10\n\\end{align*}","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve","answer":{"type":"multiline","lines":2,"layout":"column","template":"$x$ = ____\\n$y$ = ____"}},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q21","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":21,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q21","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"(a) Write down the next term in each sequence.\n\n(i) (b) $12,\\ 7,\\ 2,\\ -3,\\ -8,\\ \\dots$\n\n(c) $4,\\ 7,\\ 13,\\ 25,\\ 49,\\ \\dots$\n\n(d) Find an expression, in terms of $n$, for the $n$th term of this sequence.\n\n$5,\\ 8,\\ 11,\\ 14,\\ \\dots$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":0},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1},{"label":"(d)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q22","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":22,"marks":4,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.4","d":1,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Surface area and volume","qtype":"surface area and volume","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q22","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"A closed box in the shape of a cuboid has length 5 cm, width 4 cm and height 2 cm.\n\n(a) Calculate the volume of the box.\n\n{cm$^3$}\n\n(b) On the 1 cm$^2$ grid, complete the net of this box.\n\n%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q23","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":23,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry","Transformations and vectors"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q23","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The diagram shows two regular pentagons.\nPentagon FGHJK is an enlargement of pentagon ABCDE, centre O.\n\n%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\nFind angle AEK.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"Angle AEK ="}},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q24","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":24,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q24","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"A vertical flagpole, BD, stands on horizontal ground and is held by two ropes, AD and CD.\nAD = 15 m, BC = 10.7 m and angle DAB = 38°.\n\n%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\n(a) Using trigonometry, calculate BD.\n\n{m}\n\n(b) Calculate CD.\n\n{m}","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"BD ="}},{"label":"(b)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"CD ="}}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper13-Q25","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper13","qnum":25,"marks":5,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration","Statistics"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/19 Q25","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Jason spends 480 minutes at school each day.\nThe pie chart shows the time he spends in three of his lessons.\n\n%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\n(a) Measure the sector angle for science.\n\n(b) Work out the time, in minutes, Jason spends in English.\n\n{min}\n\n(c) Jason spends 100 minutes in geography and the rest of the day is free time.\n\nComplete the pie chart.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2},{"label":"(c)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"}]